<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-203-642  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 203 642.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Weekly  March 23 1989 n1156 p20(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A real threat or an attack of Solomonella? (includes relatedarticle on the symptoms of computer viruses)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Nicolle, Lindsay.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>IBM PC owners were warned their files may be destroyed on Jan 13,1989 by a computer virus that was expected to spread across the PCworld.andP;  Several users lost files on Jan 13, however the disasterwas not as devastating as feared.andP;  Data was recoverable.andP;  The IBMPC User Group, with over 10,000 names on its mailing list,promotes the computer virus issue.andP;  Chmn Alan Solomon runs an IBMdata recovery center.andP;  Solomon has been accused of overhyping thecomputer virus threat by comparing it to the AIDS scare in themedical world.andP;  Solomon is author of a book titled 'The ComputerVirus Crisis'.andP;  The Computer Threat Research Association is anon-profit organization for clarification of the facts aboutviruses.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Computer VirusesPreventive MaintenanceSoftware ProtectionUser GroupsCodes.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>